- d3 server setup

creates in JSS:
  the 'd3-receipts' EA,  name is hardcoded, no longer in config
  the 'd3-puppyq' EA,  name is hardcoded, no longer in config
  the 'd3-receipts' Adv. Search,  name is hardcoded
  the 'd3-puppyqs' Adv. Search,  name is hardcoded
  the categories 'd3-support', d3-package', 'd3-script'

- d3/d3admin config
  - /etc/d3.conf on d3/d3admin machines need only
    d3_server_hostname
    d3_client_user
    d3_client_pw_path

    all other values are returned in JSON response from logging in to server, including:
     - client logging
        log_file
        log_level
        log_timestamp_format
     - client_http_ropw_path (or the pw itself?)
     - client_prohibited_admin_names
     - client_expiration_allowed
     - client_expiration_policy
     - puppies (if we keep the puppies)
        puppy_notification_policy
        puppy_notification_frequency
        puppy_reboot_policy
        puppy_notify_image_path
        puppy_optout_seconds
        puppy_optout_text
        puppy_optout_image_path
        puppy_slideshow_folder_path
        puppy_display_captions
        puppy_no_captions_text
        puppy_image_size
        puppy_title
        puppy_display_secs
    - admin
        admin_make_live_script
        admin_auto_clean
        admin_auto_clean_keep_deprecated
        admin_auto_clean_keep_latest_pilots


